wow.  I had no idea the beliefs were so meticulously defined here...   maybe it is just my naivete, but I've not been so boggled down by these details (maybe thankfully so!  I didn't know it was an issue of such controversy).<br>
<br>
To my mind, God is creator of ALL things both seen and unseen.  Knowing this, I believe He is evident in ALL things (Romans 1:20) which includes the bread and the wine.  What makes this particular creation -the wheat, the grapes- separte and holy is that Christ has deemed it as such at the Last Supper. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#DEB887><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bsparrowshearth.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jeffthefinn>jeffthefinn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://webpages.charter.net/nilus/finnbutton.GIF" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Your Friendly<br>Orthodox Resource</span><br>  Posts: 69<br> <font color=#B87333>(6/27/03 12:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fsparrowshearthfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://webpages.charter.net/nilus/jfinn.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Eucharist</span><hr size=1> The Orthodox refer to the Eucharist as the Holy Mysteries, we do not define but know that when we eat and drink we are in reality eating and drinking Our Lord's Body and Blood.<br>
